-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription + month (pick latest event_id)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_enriched_subscriptions.sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with plan tier (LEFT JOIN to handle missing plans)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        p.monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier,
    monthly_price
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_user_with_company.sql
-- Join users with companies to get industry (LEFT JOIN for nullable company_id)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.name,
        u.email,
        u.company_id,
        c.industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT
    user_id,
    name,
    email,
    company_id,
    industry
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/marts/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics grouped by month, tier, and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month) AS month,
        COALESCE(s.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(u.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        COALESCE(SUM(s.monthly_price), 0) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_enriched_subscriptions') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_user_with_company') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    GROUP BY
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month),
        COALESCE(s.tier, '(unknown)'),
        COALESCE(u.industry, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
ORDER BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
